A simple ruby-script based on Tim Popes' Pathogen for easy updating vim-plugins

Prerequisites:
- ruby, rubygems
- gems rubyzip and minitar

Install:
  gem install rubyzip archive-tar-minitar
  mv ~/.vim ~/.vim.orig
  git clone git@github.com:kljohann/pathogenized.git ~/.vim
  cp ./plugins.example.idnt ./plugins.idnt

Using:
  edit ~/.vim/plugins.idnt
  run ~/.vim/bin/update_plugins

Notice that you will have to remove the corresponding directory
in ~/.vim/bundle directory manually when you remove a plugin.
